'''''Conflict and Conquest in the Islamic World: A Historical Encyclopedia''''' is a two-volume encyclopedia covering the military and political [[history of Islam]], edited by [[Alexander Mikaberidze]] and published in 2011.
The encyclopedia contains more than 600 entries from dozens of contributors, as well as a glossary, maps and photographs.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Lougen|first1=Colleen|title=Sources: Conflict and Conquest in the Islamic World: A Historical Encyclopedia|journal=Reference & User Services Quarterly|date=2012|volume=51|issue=3|url=https://journals.ala.org/rusq/article/view/3140/3268}}</ref>
