'''Ronda de Salsa''', also known as Ronda Manila or simply "Ronda," is a group dance inspired by [[Rueda de Casino]]. The dance was invented at the Asian Social Institute in an attempt to energize a disintegrating Filipino-Hispanic culture through a fusion of a local Hispanic dance called [[Pandanggo]] and a popular modern dance, [[Salsa (dance)|Salsa]], which for decades has been making waves in other Hispanic countries.<ref>An article Ronda de Salsa appears at the editorials of SalsaPowers.com http://www.salsapower.com/editorials/manila_ronda.htm</ref>

The five simple basic combinations or combo, are: Gising, Pule, Patria, Lakambini and Dolorosa.

